.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:55:{i:0;s:31:"How to Fix a Noisy Garage Door.";i:1;s:89:"The fixes for a garage door that makes a racket when it opens and closes are fairly easy.";i:2;s:36:"60 second fix for your noisy garage.";i:3;s:66:"If not you can change the settings on the opener to fix the issue.";i:4;s:65:"A squeaking garage door is annoying but luckily its easily fixed.";i:5;s:84:"Locate the source of the squeaking and then tighten or lubricate hardware as needed.";i:6;s:84:"Regular maintenance will keep the garage door from becoming too noisy in the future.";i:7;s:48:"Use these tips to keep it quiet when you use it.";i:8;s:83:"If your garage door squeaks or grinds the solution may be to lubricate the rollers.";i:9;s:92:"If a visual is helpful check out this video on how to lubricate the garage rollers properly.";i:10;s:31:"Lubricate all the Moving Parts.";i:11;s:109:"You want to start by moving the garage door manually and then spray the lubricant on all the moving parts ie.";i:12;s:48:"Pivot points hinges locks nubs armbar and stems.";i:13;s:36:"Then get down and check the rollers.";i:14;s:79:"If you have plastic rollers then you dont have to worry about lubricating them.";i:15;s:33:"How to Fix a Squeaky Garage Door.";i:16;s:112:"Replace the rollers preferably with solid nylon or nylon-coated varieties which leads to quieter door operation.";i:17;s:53:"Plus nylon rollers dont require periodic lubrication.";i:18;s:67:"Other rollers however do require lubrication at least twice a year.";i:19;s:42:"Disconnect the garage door from the motor.";i:20;s:81:"Spray the moving parts of the door as you manually move the door along the track.";i:21;s:109:"Make sure all hinges and pivot points stems and nubs and arm bars are lubricated with a lithium based grease.";i:22;s:64:"Check to see if your garage door uses a metal or plastic roller.";i:23;s:81:"Disable the automatic garage door opener by pulling on the cable that hangs down.";i:24;s:37:"Manually pull the garage door closed.";i:25;s:37:"Pull the garage open and shut slowly.";i:26;s:31:"Watch the springs in the upper.";i:27;s:98:"Here are two simple steps on how to fix a squeaky garage door and ways to prevent it from squeaky.";i:28;s:19:"Step One Lubricate.";i:29;s:50:"Lubrication is always a good choice to start with.";i:30;s:95:"To lubricate your garage door use a metal or garage lubricant for the chains and on the tracks.";i:31;s:76:"Silicone-based lubricants work better than oil-based because oil lubricants.";i:32;s:96:"Plus a squeaky garage door is often an indication of a larger and more serious structural issue.";i:33;s:67:"In short its something you need to take care of as soon as you can.";i:34;s:107:"In this post well tell you the best DIY methods when it comes to learning how to fix a squeaky garage door.";i:35;s:117:"1 Moving the door manually spray all the moving parts including the hinges pivot points stems nubs locks and arm bar.";i:36;s:20:"2 Check the rollers.";i:37;s:84:"If they are made from plastic dont worry about them greasing them wont achieve much.";i:38;s:65:"Thankfully fixing a squeaky garage door is generally pretty easy.";i:39;s:37:"Here are five steps you need to take.";i:40;s:41:"Easy Tips For Silencing Your Garage Door.";i:41;s:52:"Clean out the tracks with a clean cloth or a vacuum.";i:42;s:62:"This will help prevent the wheels from catching and squeaking.";i:43;s:73:"Lightly spray the tracks and chain with a silicone-based spray lubricant.";i:44;s:56:"Hire a Professional and Contact Top Choice Garage Doors.";i:45;s:164:"After lubricating the source of the squeak on your garage door and finding that the squeaking still persists it may be possible that parts will need to be replaced.";i:46;s:102:"It is recommended that you do not attempt to replace any parts on your own and to hire a professional.";i:47;s:85:"Lubricate the track once or twice a year when you notice uneven lifting or squeaking.";i:48;s:55:"Replace the batteries in the garage door opener remote.";i:49;s:51:"Giving the door a stronger signal may help it move.";i:50;s:80:"The top of the garage door usually has springs which also need to be lubricated.";i:51;s:66:"Spray the grease on the outside of the springs and bearing plates.";i:52;s:81:"Open and close the door a few times to spread the grease to all the moving parts.";i:53;s:143:"The rollers could be the cause of a squeaking garage door so use a garage door lubricant or silicone-based lubricant on them plus their hinges.";i:54;s:138:"The hinges that hold together the different parts of the door could also be the problem and these should also be lubricated when the door.";}}